Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: A space to call your own. A fully furnished office, complete with Business Grade data and telecoms, that grows as your business does.

This is the perfect place for you to run and grow your company while surrounded by like-minded community members.

The flexible work-spaces are made to fit you. Whether you’re a start-up, small business or freelancer, Alpha Works is designed with you in mind.

Hot Desks mean you can drop in and roam free or, if you’d prefer a more permanent spot, you can be set up with your own dedicated desk in one of our shared areas. Need something bigger? They’ve got flexible private office space for you and your team. No matter where you’re at or where you want to be, they’re here to help you realise your ambitions.

Located in a refurbished landmark building at the centre of Birmingham's prime central business district, this Birmingham Victoria Square business centre has views across Victoria Square to the stunning Town hall. This centre has 9 meeting rooms and conference suites seating 4 to 30 people. The centre also has day offices and a business lounge and benefits from air conditioning, disabled facilities, reception staff and support teams, kitchen areas, shower facilities, WiFi and state-of-the-art technology.

Stunning, premium offices in Birmingham City Centre. This is an exceptional office development in the very heart of the City that blends heritage with modernity. This striking development boasts a stunning reception, break out spaces and the offices are arranged over three floors

Discover how pro-working can provide the workspace you want in this fabulous art deco building. Just yards from New Street Station, set on the thriving Temple Street which runs to the ever-popular Cathedral Square, this is the perfect spot to locate your business.

This unique all-inclusive workspace package comes with super-fast internet, no deposits and a service excellence guarantee. Choose from co-working and shared space, to private office suites and the most flexible serviced offices Birmingham has on the market.

This contemporary, serviced office space in the Colmore District of Birmingham has an impressive double-height reception area creating a great first impression. The modern meeting rooms are located on the first and second floors of this refurbished building. The centre offers air conditioning, high-speed internet, modern kitchen facilities and disabled access. The 3 high quality meeting rooms are easy to book and have a capacity of 4 to 6 delegates. The Grand Central meeting room has a modern, grey colour scheme and seats up to 6 people, the Snow Hill and Moor Street meeting rooms seats up to 4. The Community room is also available (CM 126) this is an internal 4 person room with no TV screen.

The Crossway centre is an ideal location for your business to call home. Close to New Street and Snow Hill stations. Access is easy to the Jewellery Quarter and city centre amenities in just a few minutes walk.  The interior sports quirky, modern decor and an impressive reception area.

The Cornwall Buildings provides meeting rooms and serviced office space bang in the centre of Birmingham’s high-profile Colmore Business District. This Grade II-listed building has been fully refurbished to include air conditioning, a communal lounge, and meeting rooms as well as co-working spaces in our business lounge. The building’s interior is bright and stylish and alongside its modern, comfortable facilities the historic building has retained many period features making it a unique and striking workspace. Office space is available for 2-12 people and Cornwall Buildings are located a short stroll from the retail heart of the city and from New Street and Snow Hill stations making it the perfect location to connect with customers and other businesses.

Colmore Gate is situated in the heart of the sought after Colmore Business District. This location is perfect for commuters, with transport links by bus, rail, tram and road all within easy reach. The area has a well-balanced selection of eateries perfect for entertaining, plus an ever-expanding retail district on the door step.

The newly extended Birmingham Metro Line now reaches from Snow Hill through to the brand new Grand Central. With Snow Hill Station located directly opposite Colmore Gate, and New Street Station within a 5-minute walk, all major cities across the UK can be reached by rail. The A38M out of Birmingham provides a direct link to the M6 J6.

Birmingham Internal Airport is only a 9 minute train journey from New Street Station, or easily accessible via the M6/M42 by road.

There is a large selection of parking options in the immediate vicinity, including 2 NCP’s, the new B4 Post Box car park and parking at Snow Hill Station. Within a 10 minute walk you can reach all the City Centres major retail locations including The Bullring, The Mailbox, and Grand Central. There are several quality coffee houses, bars and restaurants, including Michelin starred Adams and Purnell’s, within proximity to the building.

The Colmore Building offers first-class facilities, including an on-site cafe, a complimentary high-tech gym, luxury washrooms and spa treatment rooms. 

Ranging from large open plan offices to one-person desks in a shared workspace, there are offices available for hire that will suit all stages of business growth. Your high end serviced office will be set up with stylish furnishings and the latest technologies, arranged to support productivity and efficiency.
